<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<TcPlcObject Version="1.1.0.1" ProductVersion="3.1.4026.18">
  <DUT Name="ST_PushMetricAggHeader" Id="{b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8b9c-0d1e-2f3a4b5c6d02}">
    <Declaration><![CDATA[(*
:Description: 52-byte fixed header of an FB_Metrics push frame.

The ``{attribute 'pack_mode' := '1'}`` pragma must be on the line **above
the TYPE keyword** (not inside the STRUCT body) ‚Äî applied inside the
struct it would only act as a per-field hint and TwinCAT would still pad
the struct's tail to 8 bytes for the LINT members.

Pushed via ADSWRITE to ``IG = 0x4D424301`` / ``IO = 2`` (IO_PUSH_METRIC_AGG).
``event_type = 21`` (PUSH_METRIC_AGG) discriminates this frame from the
existing per-task diagnostic batch (event_type=10) and UI-driven custom
metric batch (event_type=20).

Wire layout (LE, ``pack_mode := 1``):

* +0x00 ``version``       ‚Äî wire version = 2
* +0x01 ``event_type``    ‚Äî = 21 (PUSH_METRIC_AGG)
* +0x02 ``flags``         ‚Äî bit0=has_trace_ctx, bit1=ring_overflowed,
                             bit2=has_sample_ts
* +0x03 ``body_schema``   ‚Äî see ``E_MetricBodySchema``
* +0x04 ``sample_size``   ‚Äî bytes per sample in body
* +0x08 ``sample_count``  ‚Äî number of samples in body
* +0x0C ``metric_id``     ‚Äî FNV-1a hash of metric name (stable per name)
* +0x10 ``task_index``    ‚Äî owning PLC task index (1..n)
* +0x11 ``stat_mask``     ‚Äî bitmask of stats packed in body samples when
                            ``body_schema = eNumericAggregated`` (see
                            ``E_MetricStat``); 0 for raw / non-aggregated frames
* +0x12 reserved (2 B)    ‚Äî pad to 4-byte alignment
* +0x14 ``cycle_count_start`` ‚Äî task cycle counter at first sample in window
* +0x18 ``cycle_count_end``   ‚Äî task cycle counter at last sample in window
* +0x1C reserved (4 B)        ‚Äî pad to 8-byte alignment for ``dc_time_start``
* +0x20 ``dc_time_start``     ‚Äî DC time at first sample (ns since DC epoch)
* +0x28 ``dc_time_end``       ‚Äî DC time at last sample (ns since DC epoch)
* +0x30 ``name_len``          ‚Äî bytes of metric name following the optional
                                 trace context (UTF-8, max 63)
* +0x31 ``unit_len``          ‚Äî bytes of metric unit following ``name`` (UTF-8,
                                 max 15, 0 = unitless)
* +0x32 reserved (2 B)        ‚Äî pad to 52 bytes
* = 0x34 (52 B) total fixed header

After this fixed header the frame contains, in order:

1. *Optional* ‚Äî when ``flags.bit0 = 1`` ‚Äî 24 B: trace_id (16 B) + span_id (8 B).
2. ``name_len`` bytes of metric name (UTF-8, no NUL).
3. ``unit_len`` bytes of metric unit (UTF-8, no NUL).
4. Body: ``sample_count`` sample slots. Slot layout depends on
   ``flags.bit2`` (has_sample_ts):

   * ``bit2 = 0`` (default): slot = ``sample_size`` value bytes. Total body
     = ``sample_count * sample_size``. Per-sample timestamps are reconstructed
     on the receiver side by linear interpolation between ``dc_time_start``
     and ``dc_time_end``.
   * ``bit2 = 1``: slot = 2 B ``cycle_offset`` (little-endian ``u16``,
     relative to ``cycle_count_start``) followed by ``sample_size`` value
     bytes. Total body = ``sample_count * (2 + sample_size)``. The receiver
     reconstructs per-sample DC time as
     ``dc_time_start + cycle_offset * cycle_time_ns`` where
     ``cycle_time_ns`` is derived from the header span. u16 covers up to
     65 535 cycles per window ‚Äî the PLC emits an early autoflush if the
     configured push interval would exceed this.

Total frame size = 52 + (24 if has_trace_ctx else 0) + name_len + unit_len
                 + sample_count * (sample_size + (2 if has_sample_ts else 0)).
*)
{attribute 'pack_mode' := '1'}
TYPE ST_PushMetricAggHeader :
STRUCT
    nVersion           : BYTE;                      // +0x00, = 2
    nEventType         : BYTE;                      // +0x01, = 21
    nFlags             : BYTE;                      // +0x02, bit0=has_trace_ctx, bit1=ring_overflowed
    eBodySchema        : E_MetricBodySchema;        // +0x03, body interpretation tag
    nSampleSize        : UDINT;                     // +0x04, bytes per sample in body
    nSampleCount       : UDINT;                     // +0x08, samples in body
    nMetricId          : UDINT;                     // +0x0C, FNV-1a(name)
    nTaskIndex         : USINT;                     // +0x10, owning task index
    nStatMask          : BYTE;                      // +0x11, E_MetricStat bitmask (0 = raw/non-aggregated)
    aReserved0         : ARRAY [0..1] OF BYTE;      // +0x12, pad to 0x14
    nCycleCountStart   : UDINT;                     // +0x14
    nCycleCountEnd     : UDINT;                     // +0x18
    nReserved1         : UDINT;                     // +0x1C, pad to 0x20
    nDcTimeStart       : LINT;                      // +0x20
    nDcTimeEnd         : LINT;                      // +0x28
    nNameLen           : BYTE;                      // +0x30, max 63
    nUnitLen           : BYTE;                      // +0x31, max 15
    aReserved2         : ARRAY [0..1] OF BYTE;      // +0x32, pad to 52 bytes
END_STRUCT
END_TYPE
]]></Declaration>
  </DUT>
</TcPlcObject>
